.TH HUM 1 "2026-07-15" "hum" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hum \- a minimal TUI music player
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hum
.RB [ \-p | \-\-playlists ]
.RB [ \-b | \-\-browse ]
.RB [ \-s | \-\-search ]
.RB [ \-q | \-\-queue ]
.RB [ \-h | \-\-help ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hum
is a terminal music player that searches YouTube, plays audio with mpv,
and automatically downloads tracks to a local library.
It works offline once you have music saved locally.
.PP
On launch, hum shows a home screen with options to open playlists,
browse the library, search YouTube, or view the queue.
Use the flags above to skip the home screen and jump directly to a view.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-playlists
Open the playlists view.
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-browse
Browse the local library.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-search
Open the YouTube search prompt.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-queue
View the playback queue.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a help summary and exit.
.SH KEYS
.SS Navigation
.TP
.B j/k
Move down/up.
.TP
.B g/G
Jump to top/bottom.
.TP
.B Esc /
Search YouTube.
.TP
.B Esc p
Open playlists.
.TP
.B v
View the queue.
.TP
.B b
Browse the local library.
.TP
.B q
Go back to the home screen, or quit from the home screen.
.TP
.B ?
Show the in-app help page.
.SS Playback
.TP
.B l, Enter
Play the selected track. Selecting a playlist result expands it
to show its individual tracks.
.TP
.B Space
Pause or resume.
.TP
.B n
Next track.
.TP
.B p
Previous track.
.TP
.B x
Stop playback.
.TP
.B , .
Seek backward/forward 5 seconds.
.TP
.B + \-
Volume up/down.
.TP
.B m
Mute/unmute.
.TP
.B r
Cycle repeat mode (off, single, all).
.SS Queue
.TP
.B a
Add the selected track to the queue.
.TP
.B d
Delete the selected track from the queue.
.TP
.B c
Clear the entire queue (asks for confirmation).
.TP
.B J/K
Move a track down/up in the queue.
.TP
.B S
Shuffle the queue.
.TP
.B s
Save the current queue as a playlist.
.SS Playlists
.TP
.B l, Enter
Enter a playlist, or play a track inside one.
Entering a playlist loads all its tracks into the queue.
.TP
.B h
Go back one level.
.TP
.B A
Add the selected track(s) to an existing playlist.
.TP
.B d
Delete a playlist or a track from a playlist.
.TP
.B R
Rename a playlist.
.SS Search results
.TP
.B s / p
Search results are marked with
.B s
(song) or
.B p
(playlist) on the left.
.TP
.B Enter on a playlist result
Expands the playlist to show its individual tracks.
.TP
.B D
Batch download all displayed results. Prompts for a playlist name,
then lets you name each track before downloading.
.TP
.B >> download all
Appears at the bottom of an expanded playlist.
Select it and press Enter to batch download all tracks.
.SS Visual mode
.TP
.B V
Toggle visual selection. Use j/k to extend the selection,
then press a, A, or d to act on all selected tracks.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/Music/
Default library directory. Downloaded tracks are saved here as opus files.
Can be changed in config.h.
.TP
.I ~/Music/playlists/
Playlists are stored as plain text files with a .hum extension.
Each line is a tab-separated title and URL pair.
.SH CONFIGURATION
All configuration is done by editing
.B config.h
and rebuilding. This includes:
.PP
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
All keybinds
.IP \(bu 2
All colors (headers, line numbers, playing indicator, visual selection,
search bar, progress bar, home screen title/subtitle/keys/selection,
song and playlist markers, and more)
.IP \(bu 2
Library path
.IP \(bu 2
Search result count (songs and playlists separately)
.IP \(bu 2
Volume step and seek step
.RE
.PP
Build options (compiler, flags, install prefix) live in
.BR config.mk .
.SH DEPENDENCIES
.TP
.B mpv
Audio playback and IPC control.
.TP
.B yt-dlp
YouTube search and track downloading. Not needed if you only play local files.
.TP
.B ncurses
Terminal UI.
